oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Lantana School students
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group portrait of the Lantana School student body standing outside of the school building. Lantana School was one of the rural schools about five miles away from Crossville. One girl standing front center holds a chalkboard sign which reads: ""Lantana School 1911"". Note: this negative was cut in half and is only partially exposed.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Group portraits; Children; Schools;
